# skill: checkpoint
# purpose: Create git checkpoint with proper commit message and metadata
# triggers: Before any significant change, after each RPOLES phase

## Invocation
```
checkpoint --phase <phase-name> --description "<concise description>" [--next "<what comes next>"]
```

## Pre-conditions
- Git repository initialized
- Changes staged (or stage with --add <files>)

## Implementation
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# checkpoint.skill implementation

PHASE="${1}"
DESCRIPTION="${2}"
NEXT="${3:-}"
AGENT="${AGENT_NAME:-unknown-agent}"
TASK="${TASK_ID:-manual}"
TIMESTAMP=$(date -Iseconds)

# Validate phase
case "$PHASE" in
    review|plan|outline|locate|execute|ship|custom)
        ;;
    *)
        echo "Invalid phase: $PHASE"
        exit 1
        ;;
esac

# Create commit message
COMMIT_MSG='['"$PHASE"'] '"$DESCRIPTION"

if [ -n "$NEXT" ]; then
    COMMIT_MSG="$COMMIT_MSG

Next: $NEXT"
fi

COMMIT_MSG="$COMMIT_MSG

Agent: $AGENT
Task: $TASK
Checkpoint: $TIMESTAMP"

# Commit
git commit -m "$COMMIT_MSG"

echo "✓ Checkpoint created: [$PHASE] $DESCRIPTION"
```

## Usage Examples
```
checkpoint --phase review --description "Requirements analyzed, 2 clarifications needed" --next "Wait for clarifications before planning"
checkpoint --phase execute --description "Auth module implemented with tests" --next "Handoff to QA for validation"
```
